		<h2>Software</h2>
	
		<p><a title="Cycling '74" href="http://www.cycling74.com/">Max/MSP</a> is a visual programming language.  It's like code, but with objects and patch cables and sliders where brackets and semicolons usually are.  I've used Max/MSP for the past three years to develop concepts to bridge the gap between audio and video.  Check back for updates soon.</p>
	
		<h3><em>Motion Music</em> (in conjunction with Stephen Fortunato)</h3>
		<h4>Motion-based Mixing</h4>
		<h4><a title="Sound Art Showcase 2011: Stephen Fortunato" href="http://facultypages.scad.edu/~aruschko/SoundArtWebsite/Stephen%20Fortunato.html/">SCAD Sound Art Showcase 2011</a></h4>
		<p>Uses motion detection to dynamically mix tracks in an audio file; more motion causes more tracks to sound.</p>

		<h3><em>Ambience</em></h3>
		<h4>Reactive Audiovisual Stimulus</h4>
		<%= image_tag("Ambience1_500.png", alt: "Ambience Screenshot") %>
		<p>A field of color squares and a set of oscillators are driven by a semi-random algorithm.  Both visual and aural stimulus are dynamically altered via detection of motion, ambient light, and color.  The squares more or less reflect the averaged color of the camera's input.  Intended as a sort of reactive wall art.</p>
